OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1771878200
OL,3,CPowerful drug cartel leader 'El
OL,4,CMencho' killed by Mexican army
OL,6,FIn Guadalajara, the state capital,
OL,7,Fburning vehicles blocked roads.
OL,8,FMexico's second-largest city is
OL,9,Fscheduled to host matches during this
OL,10,Fsummer's soccer World Cup.
OL,12,FThe US State Department warned US
OL,13,Fcitizens in Jalisco, Tamaulipas,
OL,14,FMichoacan, Guerrero and Nuevo Leon
OL,15,Fstates to remain in safe places due to
OL,16,Fthe ongoing security operations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
