OL,3,CPowerful drug cartel leader 'El
OL,4,CMencho' killed by Mexican army
OL,6,FOseguera Cervantes, 59, was originally
OL,7,Ffrom Aguililla in the neighbouring
OL,8,Fstate of Michoacan. He had been
OL,9,Fsignificantly involved in drug
OL,10,Ftrafficking activities since the 1990s.
OL,12,FWhen he was younger, he migrated to
OL,13,Fthe US, where he was convicted of
OL,14,Fconspiracy to distribute heroin in the
OL,15,FDistrict Court for the Northern
OL,16,FDistrict of California in 1994 and
OL,17,Fserved nearly three years in prison.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1771878200
OL,3,CPowerful drug cartel leader 'El
OL,4,CMencho' killed by Mexican army
OL,6,FFollowing his release from custody,
OL,7,FOseguera Cervantes returned to Mexico
OL,8,Fand reengaged in drug trafficking,
OL,9,Feventually going on to create the
OL,10,FJalisco New Generation Cartel around
OL,11,F2007.
OL,13,FInitially, they worked for the Sinaloa
OL,14,FCartel, but eventually split and for
OL,15,Fyears the two cartels have battled for
OL,16,Fterritory across Mexico.
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/12
